TI  - Guidance for establishing the mitigation impact potential of GCF funded activities in support of Decision B.33/12
AU  - Fund, Green Climate
T2  - Green Climate Fund
AB  - The Governing Instrument for the Green Climate Fund (GCF) outlines that the Fund's purpose is to promote a shift towards low-emission, climate-resilient development by supporting developing countries in reducing greenhouse gas emissions and adapting to climate change. This focus particularly considers the needs of countries most vulnerable to climate impacts. GCF Board Decision [decision:B.33/12] further emphasizes this requirement by establishing principles for demonstrating the impact potential of GCF-funded activities.
